==Walkthrough==
===Undead chickens===
'''''Items needed:''' A [[ghostspeak amulet]], [[Ectophial]], and 20 [[ecto-tokens]] (bring 4 empty [[pot]]s, 4 empty [[bucket]]s and 4 bones if you wish to obtain the tokens during the quest)''
{{Checklist|
*Talk to [[Ava]] in the west wing of [[Draynor Manor]] and complete the dialogue. {{Chat option|1I would be happy to make your home into a better place.}}
*Go to the [[undead chicken]] farm west of the [[Ectofuntus]] with your [[ghostspeak amulet]] and [[ecto-token]]s (or materials for them), and talk to [[Alice]]. {{Chat option|4I'm here about a quest.}}
*Keep talking between Alice and [[Alice's husband]] in the cow pen 4 times until she tells you to go to talk to the [[old crone]] for an amulet.
*Run west of the farm until you reach the old crone's house just east of the [[Slayer Tower]].
*Speak twice to the old crone to receive a [[crone-made amulet]]. {{Chat option|2I'm here about the farmers east of here.}}
*Speak with Alice's husband to give him the Crone-made amulet. {{Chat option|1Okay, you need it more than I do, I suppose.}}
*Speak with Alice's husband again.
*After the cutscene, speak to Alice's husband who will now sell you two [[undead chicken]]s for 20 [[ecto-token]]s. {{Chat option|1Could I buy those chickens now?|2Could I buy two chickens?}}
}}
===Magnet===
'''''Items needed:''' 5 [[iron bar]]s, a [[hammer]], [[Skills necklace]] for teleport to [[Crafting Guild]], and your two [[undead chicken]]s.''
{{Checklist|
*Take your 5 iron bars, hammer, and two undead chickens back to the west wing of Draynor Manor and speak to [[Ava]].
*Speak to the [[Witch]] in the north-west corner of Draynor Manor (inside the building).
*Speak to the Witch again to receive a [[selected iron]].
*Take the selected iron to the centre of the [[Rimmington mine]], face north, and use the hammer on it.
*Return to Ava and give her the magnet.
}}
===Undead twigs===
'''''Items needed:''' [[Mithril axe]], [[polished button]], [[hard leather]], [[games necklace]] for teleport to [[Burthorpe]], and a [[holy symbol]]''
[[File:Translated notes interface.png|thumb|right|Translated notes]]
{{Checklist|
*Talk to Ava.
*Use your axe on an [[Undead tree]] (not Dead tree). You can exit through the door of the east room. (An Undead tree is found in front of the manor, has a yellow examine option.)
*Talk to Ava after it fails to chop the Undead tree. She will tell you to bring your Mithril axe and [[Holy symbol]] to [[Turael]] in [[Burthorpe]].
*Talk to Turael, the [[slayer master]] in a house in south-eastern [[Burthorpe]]. {{Chat option|4I'm here about a quest.}}
*Talk to Turael again to receive the [[Blessed axe]], provided you have a Mithril axe and a Holy symbol in your inventory. {{Chat option|4Hello, I'm here about those trees again.|1I'd love one, thanks.}}
*Return to the mansion and cut the undead tree again.
*Bring the [[Undead twigs]] to Ava.
*Talk to Ava again, and she will give you garbled [[Research notes (Animal Magnetism)|research notes]] that you need to solve.
**To translate turn off all the green orbs except for the 2nd, 5th, and 9th (left to right, see image)
*Talk to Ava again.
*Combine the [[A pattern|solved notes]] with the polished button and the hard leather.
*Give the container to Ava.}}
'''Quest complete!'''

